# Next.js Rules

## Core Principles

- Use **App Router only** (`app/` directory).
- Prefer **Server Components by default**.
- Use **Client Components only when necessary**.

---

## Rendering Strategy

- Default to Server Components.
- Use `"use client"` only when needed:
  - useState
  - useEffect
  - event handlers
  - browser APIs

Example:

```tsx
"use client";

export default function Button() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>{count}</button>;
}
```

---

## Data Fetching

- Fetch data in Server Components when possible.
- Use Supabase server client in server layer.
- Use React Query only for client-side needs.

Bad:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  fetch("/api/persons");
}, []);
```

Good:

```tsx
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await getPersons();
  return <div>{data.length}</div>;
}
```

---

## Folder Structure (App Router)

```
app/
  layout.tsx
  page.tsx
  (routes)/
    members/
      page.tsx
      [id]/
        page.tsx
```

- Use route groups `( )` for organization
- Use dynamic routes `[id]`
- Use nested layouts when needed

---

## API Routes (Route Handlers)

- Use `route.ts` for backend endpoints.
- Prefer Supabase RPC instead of heavy API logic.

Example:

```
app/api/members/route.ts
```

---

## Server Actions

- Use Server Actions for mutations when possible.
- Keep logic close to UI when it improves simplicity.

Example:

```ts
"use server";

export async function createMember(data: FormData) {
  await supabase.from("persons").insert(data);
}
```

---

## Caching & Performance

- Use Next.js caching strategies correctly:
  - `force-cache` for static data
  - `no-store` for dynamic data
- Use `revalidate` when needed.

Example:

```ts
fetch(url, { cache: "no-store" });
```

---

## Metadata

- Use `metadata` API for SEO.
- Always define page metadata.

Example:

```ts
export const metadata = {
  title: "Family Tree",
  description: "Manage your family tree",
};
```

---

## Navigation

- Use `next/navigation`:
  - `useRouter`
  - `useParams`
  - `usePathname`

Avoid old `next/router`.

---

## Error Handling

- Use `error.tsx` for route-level errors.
- Use `not-found.tsx` for missing data pages.

---

## Anti-patterns (DO NOT DO)

- ❌ Mixing server + client logic in one component unnecessarily
- ❌ Using `useEffect` for data fetching in App Router
- ❌ Overusing Client Components
- ❌ Putting business logic inside pages
- ❌ Ignoring caching strategy

---

## Goal

Write Next.js code that is:

- Server-first
- Performance optimized
- Cleanly separated
- Scalable for large apps